Flags that are use in the Docker run commands

====================================================================================

To create a container from an image
$ docker run image_name 

====================================================================================
-it => for opening an interactive terminal in a docker

--name => used for giving a name to a container

-d => Used for a running a container in detached mode as a backgroud process

-e => Used for passing environment variables to the container

-p => used for mapping between port of container with the dockerhost port

-P => Used for automatic port mapping 
        ie: it will map internal port of the container with some port on host machine
        This host port will be some number greater than 30000

-v => Used for attaching a volume to the container

--volume-from => Used for sharing volume between containers

--network => Used to run container on a specific network

--link => Used for linking the container for creating a multi container architecture

--memory => Used for specify the maximum amount of ram that the container can use

